    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Moving to Octopress]]></title>
    <link href="http://monzell.github.io/blog/2013/11/04/moving-to-octopress/"/>
    <updated>2013-11-04T21:29:00-06:00</updated>
    <id>http://monzell.github.io/blog/2013/11/04/moving-to-octopress</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>As you can see, I have moved blogs. Hopefully I can keep up with it.</p>

<p>Things have busy for me. I have moved from Atlanta to Chicago, as well as jobs &ndash; from AT&amp;T to Sears, back to AT&amp;T and finally at my current role in Ex Libris. A future update will provide insight as to my reasons why.</p>

<p>Anyway, using Octopress is going to be a big change, after using online blogging services such as Tumblr and Blogger. In some ways, it is more work with the association frustration at dealing with the sometimes rickty nature of Ruby&rsquo;s dependencies. In other ways, it felt liberating to be post by running:</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>server:octopress rilindo$ bundle exec rake new_post["I should put something here"]
</span><span class='line'>server:octopress rilindo$ emacs source/_posts/2013-10-29-i-should-put-something-here.markdown 
</span><span class='line'>server:octopress rilindo$ bundle exec rake generate
</span><span class='line'>server:octopress rilindo$ bundle exec rake deploy</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>Here, I generated a new post, added content, generate the code, then post it. It feels so hackish. :)</p>

<p>Incidentally, ordinarily you would run just &ldquo;rake&rdquo;, but with Ruby 2.0, it appears to be failing:</p>

<figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>server:octopress rilindo$ rake new_post["Moving to Octopress"]
</span><span class='line'>rake aborted!
</span><span class='line'>You have already activated rake 10.1.0, but your Gemfile requires rake 0.9.2.2. Using bundle exec may solve this.
</span><span class='line'>/Users/rilindo/blog/octopress/Rakefile:2:in `&lt;top (required)&gt;'
</span><span class='line'>(See full trace by running task with --trace)</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>


<p>So [bundle exec] it is&hellip;</p>
]]></content>
